# CI: Monitor build after push

When you push to `main` (or trigger a Release workflow), always monitor the build and report the outcome:

1. **After `git push origin main`**: Run `gh run watch --repo yavik-kapadia/demo-time --exit-status` (or `./scripts/push-and-watch.sh` to push and watch in one go) and report whether the build succeeded or failed. If it failed, fetch the failed logs with `gh run view <run-id> --log-failed` and fix or summarize the error.

2. **Alternative**: Use `gh run list --repo yavik-kapadia/demo-time --workflow "Release" --limit 1` to get the latest run ID, then `gh run view <id> --repo yavik-kapadia/demo-time` or `gh run view <id> --log-failed` to report status.

Do not skip this step when the user has asked for a push or when you have just pushed.
